<p>That same evening, the biracial, bisexual, and bipolar belter released a digital deluxe edition of her third studio album Manic.</p>

<p>The new version of her expanded LP (which originally hit shelves January 17) features new songs Wipe Your Tears and I'm Not Mad, as well as stripped-back reworkings of the record's original tracks.</p>

<p>What's more, Halsey (born Ashley Frangipane) also dropped a nostalgic music video for 929, which features footage of herself as a child.</p>

